The paper discusses the use of runtime monitoring for verifying the correctness of programs developed in Node.js and Node-RED, which are both related to software engineering (cs.SE). The focus is on the Internet of Things (IoT) systems, which involves security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of a dynamic analysis framework (Jalangi), which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper discusses the language and system agnostic nature of trace expressions, which can be applied to various systems and domains, including cyber-physical systems (cs.SY).
